<statement>
<p>Solve the equation: <m>\displaystyle{15}{\left({10}^{{{6}{x}}}\right)}-{2}={0}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=</m><fillin characters="6" /> </p>
<p>Round to 3 decimal places.</p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>-0.146</li></ul></p><p><m>\displaystyle{15}{\left({10}^{{{6}{x}}}\right)}-{2}={0}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{15}{\left({10}^{{{6}{x}}}\right)}=-{2}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{10}^{{{6}{x}}}=-\frac{{2}}{{15}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{x}={\log{{\left(-\frac{{2}}{{15}}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{\log{{\left(-\frac{{2}}{{15}}\right)}}}}{{6}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}\approx-{0.146}</m></p>
</solution>
</myopenmath>

